The paper discusses the design of radio access techniques for 5G wireless networks, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses issues related to user fairness, spectral efficiency, and reliability, which are relevant to System and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper clarifies misunderstandings related to security and interference, which are relevant to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
